https://instagram.com/_pocketss_?utm_medium=copy_link</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/cYFEOPm</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[DumpsterKoala]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>ArtCrawl 2022. Hello fellow artists. I salvage scrap vintage 1940s, 50s, and 60s microphones and bring them back to life as LED desk lamps.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/2KGE6Zq</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/dHzAXU8.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Some of my wares, some sexy seniors. The dirty pictures are at the end.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/GYSLudU.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>1950s Olson M105s</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/OnWXGat.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>1950s Monarch TM-16. May look familiar if you’ve ever been Rick rolled.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/VcMXO2T.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>1950s Shure Monoplex 737. Beauty! They don’t make them like this anymore.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/ynnbZBK.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>‘BROADCAST’ a Modern reproduction on the left. On the right, 1960s Olson M102. My handy road show kit for the road.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/LTS12pt.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>1940s Shure 702D on the gooseneck and upper right an Electrovoice Mercury 911.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/PB7aT3f.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>1950s Shure 51s</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/GuFyDzL.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>1950s CLASSIC Shure 55s. Masculine profile. Feminine curves. Mmmmm. I cant stop! They’re all over the house!!</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/9rT3uZe.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Matched Pair of 1960s Japan Realistic 33-999</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/DR3yHNl.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Serious processes going down in the shop. Usual multi-step cleaning and sterilizing before the bodywork even starts.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/MoNcFFh.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>A before and after of this poor guy, a Shure Motarola CR81A circa 1950s.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/1bzJI2y.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Umm. Yeah. They can be pretty disgusting after the first 70-80 years.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/f03CRZp.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Thanks for looking! Cat Tax, vintage microphones made into lamps makes Mason sleepy.  -Edit. Trying to fix link. And FP! Holy cow. Thank you guys for the love!!! My store… etsy.com/shop/BattleStationLight</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/2KGE6Zq</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[BattleStationLighting]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Cool.  Terrorist threat?</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/cWmNwVK</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/C1btG0Q.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/w7Dje5W.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Tweet link : https://twitter.com/kendallybrown/status/1484556559287996424?s=20</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/yEfslgB.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/cWmNwVK</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Mech0T1]]></dc